A loyal servant of Imperial General Hobart who fights for the glory of the Empire. After being tempered in combat, he excels at both offense and defense. His biggest regret is not mastering ranged combat skills.
The sisters of the Elven warrior Vieruodis who despise the Undead. With their acute Elven reflexes and superior perception. they're not permitted to wear armor to protect themselves.
These creatures are at the bottom of the demon hierarchy, and as such, they only pose a threat when attacking as a group. they're usually assigned as reconnaissance troops.
As one of the most hardworking members of the Orc race, they're forced to do almost all the menial tasks. If their overseers find out that they're being lazy, they're swiftly whipped into place.

Due to the traits of their race, these creatures have an incredibly strong physique, but also very poor eyesight, meaning they can only see buildings. Under the right circumstances, they become ruthless siege machines.

In order to thank the Dwarves for their help, the Machinists made muskets for them. In addition to hunting, the Dwarves also use them to slay their enemies, who have no hope of escape when locked onto.
The chivalrous Machinists have no concept of gender. They’re extremely powerful in hand-to-hand combat, and also extremely helpful around the farm when the Humans are harvesting their crops.
The backbone of the Orc race. In order to carry enough firepower, they don’t normally wear any armor. They can cause a lot of trouble when their enemies ignore them.
Undead that have just awakened from the necropolis. Their fragile but dexterous bodies often cause their enemies to underestimate them.

A necromancer who studies in the art of explosions. He doesn’t seem very interested in spells, but seeing an explosion really gets him excited. However, his fragile body doesn’t allow him to throw bombs into the air.
The greatest of the Human empire’s elite troops with superb combat skills. She often brags that she can “Take down ten men at once!" However, she’s not very good at fighting enemies in mid-air.
The Machinists air combat skills make up for the Empire’s weakness in the skies. However, they can only use their propellers to attack the enemy.
Although this Fire Dragon is 100 years old, she’s still considered a whelp. She can breathe flames on the battlefield to deal area damage.

A terrifying siege cart used exclusively by the Orcs. Its sudden acceleration makes it hard to defend against. When it hits a building. When it’s destroyed, the Orcs grab their axes and fight to the death.
After the Skeleton Dragons were single-handedly defeated by the Archmage, they no longer act alone. The fire they breathe deals area damage.
An Archmage skilled in the use of fire. Her idol is a sorceress called “Lina Inverse”, and she often fantasizes about being able to cast the “Dragon Slash” spell.
A weapon used by the Machinists in crucial battles. Its powerful defense and melee damage make it unstoppable. However, it can be slow when moving and attacking.

Wolf Cavalry are as fast as the wind and as brutal as fire. They were born to plunder and use their superior speed to attack buildings up close. They can also leap over rivers, making them excellent looters.
A necromancer from hell that can summon Undead Mobs whenever he needs them. He knows an advanced undead spell that can cause area damage.
The Orcs' main air units. Their slogan is "justice rains down from heaven". However, their gliders are not very firm and aren't as good as real dragon wings.

The Machinists' ultimate anti-building weapon. If you see one appear above your building. Besides the terrifying damage they cause, they also drop huge bombs after they're destroyed that cause area damage.
She hides her beauty so that others don't look down on her. Don't underestimate her strength. After charging, her next attack deals great damage to single units.

Although she's an Undead and is no longer afraid of death, her extra shield helps her feel more at ease. Every time she swings her weapon. Her undead horse allows her to deal a lot of damage when she charges.
An automatic siege machine made by the Machinists. Its low consumption and fast speed allow it to rush towards buildings without fear. Only explosions can make its soul return to the Nexus.
A mob formed of multiple Undead. Their cooperation greatly increases the Undead army’s strength.
An elite Undead sniper. He was shot in the knee last year, but it didn't affect his shooting range. His weak body doesn't slow down his arrows.
An elite version of regular Orcs. Their slogan is "Liberty is greater than life". They’re more powerful than regular Orcs, and can deal more damage with a higher attack speed.
The Orcs once heard that someone flew to the moon on a cannonball, so they started putting Peons in boxes and firing them everywhere. Of course, the leaders never worried about how they ended up.
An Orc defense building that can provide suppressing fire on the ground. However, when it was built, they forgot to add a skylight, so it can't attack flying units.

An Undead army building. The necropolis summons new Undead. When they’re first summoned, the Undead have no idea what the future holds for them.you can still see the last 4 Undead that were resurrected.
A Human defense building. The damage it causes to the enemy increases over time. No matter how tough the enemy is, it’s only a matter of time before they’re defeated by it.
A Machinist attack building that can destroy the enemy's defense towers on the other side of the river. It has a very high range and an amazing firing speed.
An Orc army building. Every once in a while, whipped Peons appear outside it. When this happens, the Peons don’t slack off. “Quit being lazy. Back to work!”
A Human army building where soldiers rest. No matter what, make sure you don’t wake the soldiers up.
Get all your archers to fire ranged shots at the enemies and the damage to defense towers will be greatly reduced.
Have you ever seen a fireball as big as a wok? It can cause a lot of damage to enemies in a small range and can greatly reduce the damage dealt to defense towers.

I hope you have a lightning rod with you. The lightning strikes three troops or buildings in range with the highest HP and briefly stuns them. In addition, the damage dealt to defense towers is greatly reduced.
Magic summons a rushing wave that mercilessly drowns everything before it. The damage dealt to defense towers will be greatly reduced.
A huge snowball that can deal ranged damage and slows down enemies. It greatly reduces damage dealt to defense towers. You don't want to be hit by this at Christmas.
Freezes enemies within a certain range, making them unable to move and attack. “Stop! Don't move”. Greatly reduces the damage dealt to defense towers.

DYOR (Do Your Own Research) is a common thing to hear when discussing blockchain investments. Managing your risk is an important key when investing into decentralized finance. 
Binance Academy said it well: "DYOR aims to reduce the number of uninformed investors in cryptocurrency. It encourages them to research and understand a cryptocurrency before investing so that they can answer precisely why they are buying that currency and supporting that project. The term is also often used as a disclaimer when cryptocurrency traders and enthusiasts make public posts or share their market analyses on social media platforms."
